# c2658616f6874eb7a6cf59707ae396eb
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:3
msgid "Choose Dataset(s)"
msgstr "Such dir ein Datenset!"

# f3df830ab96a4beab57cfd49f3d90380
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:5
msgid ""
"Choosing the dataset(s) you plan to make open is the first step to take – "
"though remember the whole opening up data process is iterative and you can "
"return to this step if you encounter problems later on."
msgstr "Als ersten Schritt sollten Sie die zu öffenden Datensätze auswählen. Falls es mit dem ausgewählten Datensatz später Probleme geben sollte können Sie natürlich immer wieder zu diesem Schritt zurückkehren."

# 4681181360a34803b412892ad689c15a
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:9
msgid ""
"If you already know exactly what dataset(s) you plan to open up you can move"
" straight on to the next section. However, in many cases, especially for "
"large institutions, choosing what datasets to focus on is a challenge. How "
"should one proceed in this case?"
msgstr "Wenn sie bereits genau wissen, welche Daten sie der Öffentlichkeit zugänglich machen wollen, können sie direkt weiter zum nächsten Schritt springen.  Oft ist jedoch die genaue Fokussierung der Datenauswahl, insbesondere für große Organisationen und Institutionen, eine große Herausforderung. Wie kann man in diesem Fall vorgehen? "

# c3395bf71cae40469b8ebdb781d2201a
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:14
msgid ""
"Creating this list should be a quick process that identifies which datasets "
"could be made open to start with. There will be time at later stages to "
"check in detail whether each dataset is suitable."
msgstr "Eine Liste mit den in Frage kommenden Datensätzen zu erstellen sollte kein großes Problem sein und in ist in der Regel in einem kurzen Prozess zu erreichen."

# a28cc6f21d52488ca51117263acf22af
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:18
msgid ""
"There is **no requirement** to create a comprehensive list of your datasets."
" The main point to bear in mind is whether it is feasible to publish this "
"data at all (whether openly or otherwise) - example see the ‘What Data’ "
"section above."
msgstr "Es ist nicht notwendig, ein komplettes Register der eigenen Daten zu erstellen. WIchtig ist nur zu klären, ob es sinnnvoll und Machbar ist, diese Daten zu veröffentlichen. Wenn man Unsicher ist, ob die Daten für Anwender nützlich sind, gibt es einen einfachen Tipp:"

# 594596464844487b8f7ab9c64f4f3ff3
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:21
msgid "Asking the community"
msgstr "Frag die Community!"

# efa094bb13e7444cb2361b9ab47b6ee2
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:23
msgid ""
"We recommend that you ask the community in the first instance. That is, the "
"people who will be accessing and using the data, are likely to have a good "
"understanding of which data are valuable."
msgstr "WIr halten es für sinnvoll, die Community zu fragen und am Prozess der Öffnung zu beteiligen. Welche Daten sind interessant, welche Formate helfen weiter? Doch wie geht man vor?"

# c4eae260f3cc4cb09a148874486910b6
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:28
msgid ""
"Prepare a short list of potential datasets that you would like feedback on. "
"It is not essential that this list concurs with what your expectations are, "
"the main intention is to get a feel for the demand. This could be based on "
"other countries' :term:`open data` catalogues."
msgstr ""

# 18f070509cf64bd8bd310c0177929b78
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:33
msgid "Create a request for comment."
msgstr "Erstellen Sie eine einfache Website zu ihren Fragestellungen"

# b9bb67542d83437cbbc07594cf757168
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:35
msgid ""
"Publicise your request with a webpage. Make sure that it is possible to "
"access the request on its own URL. That way, when shared via social media, "
"the request can be easily found."
msgstr "Stellen Sie sicher, dass die Website über eine eindeutige URL zu erreichen ist, damit Leute einfach darauf zugreifen können und die Adresse weiterverbreiten."

# 35f90b3b9f074e9d8dafbb073ed7fd7c
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:39
msgid ""
"Provide easy ways to submit responses. Avoid requiring registration, as it "
"reduces the number of responses."
msgstr "Geben sie den Nutzern die Möglichkeit, direkt über die Website Daten-Anfragen an sie zu richten, beispielsweise über E-Mail oder über ein einfaches Formular."

# 268135d011a545188337e5a65e4539ab
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:42
msgid ""
"Circulate the request to relevant mailing lists, forums and individuals "
"pointing back to the main webpage."
msgstr "Verteilen sie ihre Bitte um Feedback mit dem Link zu der entsprechenden Webseite an relevante Gruppen, Verteiler, Mailinglisten und Foren."

# f46e5a245e8c4864bc8f3a759d6e88e4
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:45
msgid ""
"Run a consultation event. Make sure you run it at a convenient time where "
"the average business person, data wrangler and official can attend."
msgstr "[Optional] Laden sie zu einer Veranstaltung ein, bei der sie Nutzer persönlich treffen können. Achten sie dabei darauf, dass auch berufstätige eine Möglichkeit haben, daran teilzunehmen."

# dc21ba29d2c34f4d87a2aeb1889d1250
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:49
msgid ""
"Ask a politician to speak on your agency's behalf. Open data is very likely "
"to be part of a wider policy of increasing access to government information."
msgstr "Bitten SIe auch Politiker an der Veranstaltung teilzunehmen. Offene Daten sind immer auch eine politische Entscheidung."

# ab8c662893d2451b88cffe39bcdd3211
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:55
msgid "Cost basis"
msgstr "Kosten"

# db1c9d150a7c4403aca7135230e19f06
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:57
msgid ""
"How much money do agencies spend on the collection and maintainence of data "
"that they hold? If they spend a great deal on a particular set of data, then"
" it is highly likely that others would like access it."
msgstr "Wie viel Geld geben Behörden für ein spezielles Datenset aus? Wenn die Erhebung, Aufbereitung und Pflege der Daten viel Geld kostet, ist es wahrscheinlich, das es sich um ein potentiell beliebtes Datenset handeln könnte."

# 3164d8e6afe74e699771de5cf4d9679a
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:61
msgid ""
"This argument may be fairly susceptible to concerns of freeriding. The "
"question you will need to respond to is, \"Why should other people get "
"information for free that is so expensive?\". The answer is that the expense"
" is aborbed by the public secotr to perform a particular function. The cost "
"of sending that data, once it has been collected, to a third party is "
"approximately nothing. Therefore, they should be charged nothing."
msgstr "Dieses Argument könnte Sorgen vor Trittbrettfahrern aufwerfen. Wieso sollen Leute kostenlosen Zugang zu so teuren Daten bekommen?\n\nDie Antwort darauf ist jedoch recht einfach: Die Daten wurden im Auftrag der öffentlichkeit und unter Verwendung öffentlicher Gelder erhoben. Die Frage lautet also: Wieso sollte die Öffentlichkeit noch ein zweites Mal für diese Daten bezahlen?"

# 67c64e4e4d8944d68fe9c7781c5a90f6
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:69
msgid "Ease of release"
msgstr "Einfachheit der öffnung"

# 84f51d9c13504089b6e7799954b47059
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:71
msgid ""
"Sometimes, rather than decide which data would be most valuable, it could be"
" useful to take a look at which data is easiest to get into the public's "
"hands. Small, easy releases can act as the catalyst for larger behavioural "
"change within organisations."
msgstr "In einzelfällen kann es sinnvoll sein, nicht die großen, prestigeträchtigen Datensätze als erstes zu veröffentlichen, sondern die kleinen, leicht zu öffnenden Perlen. Dieser Ansatz kann als Strategie genutzt werden *einfach anzufangen* mit dem Daten öffnen."

# 0391ee7dc7274ac5a1f45448596479d3
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:76
msgid ""
"Be careful with this approach however. It may be the case that these small "
"releases are of so little value that nothing is built from them. If this "
"occurs, faith in the entire project could be undermined."
msgstr "Seien Sie jedoch vorsichtig mit diesem Ansatz. Es kann sein, dass diese kleinen Datensätze von so geringem Wert, dass daraus keine guten Beispiele entstehen. Wenn dies geschieht, könnte der Glaube an das gesamte Projekt untergraben werden."

# 189f8e35114145a0a0813a96e3b224b7
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:81
msgid "Observe peers"
msgstr "Schau dich um."

# 0399cb2f9c544474888b0183d7c407c4
#: how-to-open-up-data/choose-datasets.rst:83
msgid ""
"Open data is growing movement. There are likely to be many people in your "
"area who understand what other areas are doing. Formulate a list on the "
"basis of what those agencies are doing."
msgstr "Die Open Data Bewegung wächst. Es ist nicht unwahrscheinlich, dass es in ihrer Region / in ihrem Arbeitsumfeld leute gibt, die sich damit auf kennen."

# a88c501df5ca4c8eac8af10d6166c268
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:3
msgid "How to Open up Data"
msgstr "Wie kann ich (als Behörde, Verwaltung, Organisation, ...) eigentlich Daten öffnen?"

# 8d65e16af7f94ae7a0dc6687a6d62eac
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:5
msgid ""
"This section forms the core of this manual. It gives concrete, detailed "
"advice on how data holders can open up data. Here we’ll go through the "
"basics, but also cover the pitfalls. Lastly, we will discuss the more subtle"
" issues that can arise."
msgstr "Dieses Kapitel beschreibt den Kern dieses Handbuchs. Es gibt Eigentümern konkrete und detaillierte Hilfestellung bei der Offenlegung ihrer Daten. Es werden die Grundlagen erläutert sowie einige Stolpersteine und Probleme beschrieben, die es zu vermeiden gilt."

# 35313f40f3eb4452a45ebf6fa51e48f3
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:10
msgid "There are three key rules we recommend following in opening up data:"
msgstr "Wir empfehlen, dass sie sich an zwei Regeln halten:"

# c8b2e18d854b4b7aa7b9ed2b7ca252fd
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:12
msgid ""
"**Keep it simple.** Start out small, simple and fast. There is no "
"requirement that every dataset must be made open right now. Starting out "
"opening up just one dataset, or even one part of a large dataset is fine -- "
"of course the more datasets you can open up the better."
msgstr "**Halten sie es einfach.** Fangen sie klein, einfach und schnell an. Niemand verlangt Vollständigkeit am ersten Tag. Es ist völlig in Ordnung, wenn sie mit einem Datensatz oder nur einem einzigen Teil einer großen Datensammlung anfangen. Längerfristig sollte natürlich das Ziel sein, mehr und vollständigere Daten zu veröffentlichen."

# 09bba26f149042f6b7ff1691a197f866
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:17
msgid ""
"Remember this is about innovation. Moving as rapidly as possible is good "
"because it means you can build momentum and learn from experience -- "
"innovation is as much about failure as success and not every dataset will be"
" useful."
msgstr "Denken sie daran, dass es hier um Innovation geht. Schnelles Handeln ist gut, denn es ermöglicht das Entstehen einer Eigendynamik und erleichtert das Lernen aus Erfahrung. Innovation bedeutet auch, dass nicht nur Erfolge zu erwarten sein werden. Nicht jedes Datenangebot, dass sie der Öffentlichkeit anbieten können, wird auf große Nachfrage stoßen oder gleichermaßen großen Nutzen bringen."

# d9c4ba77c1454e90b25935fbb690a66d
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:22
msgid ""
"**Engage early and engage often.** Engage with actual and potential users "
"and reusers of the data as early and as often as you can. Be they citizens, "
"businesses, developers. This will ensure that the next iteration of your "
"service is as relevant as it can be."
msgstr "**Schalten sie sich ein.** Treten sie in Kontakt mit den tatsächlichen und potenziellen Nutzern ihrer Daten, so oft und so früh wie möglich. Egal, ob es Bürger, Unternehmen oder Entwickler sind."

# bc60bdf0269a4bc3bdc9a87fa4ae8dc5
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:27
msgid ""
"It is essential to bear in mind that much of the data will not reach "
"ultimate users directly but rather via ‘info-mediaries’. These are the "
"people who take the data and transform ot remix it be presented. For example"
" most of us don’t want or need a large database of GPS coordinates, we would"
" much prefer a map. Thus, engage with infomediaries first. They will reuse "
"and repurpose the material."
msgstr "Behalten sie im Hinterkopf, dass ihre Daten häufig auf indirektem Weg an die Endnutzer gelangen, über Vermittler, die diese zur Darstellung oder Auswertung aufbereiten. Beispielsweise lesen wir als Endkonsumenten von Daten typischerweise Längen- und Breitengrade, sondern wünschen uns Kartendarstellungen. Behalten sie daher die Vermittler as wichtigste Nutzegruppe ihrer Daten besonders im Blick."

# 5c92de8a3bf24cb48e3c28969758bad0
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:34
msgid ""
"**Address common fears and misunderstandings**. This is especially important"
" if you are working with or within large institutions such as government. "
"When opening up data you will encounter plenty of questions and fears. It is"
" important to (a) identify the the most important ones and (b) address them "
"at as an early stage as possible."
msgstr "**Sprechen sie typische Ängste und Missverständnisse direkt an** - das ist besonders wichtig, wenn sie Teil einer großen Institution oder einr Regierung sind. Mit der Offenlegung von Daten werden sie zahlreiche Fragen (und Ängste) aufwerfen. Es ist wichtig, (a) die wichtigsten zu identifizieren und (b) sie so früh wie möglich offen zu adressieren."

# 9a125583109b4b45a81d6d5439fe29dc
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:40
msgid ""
"There are 4 main steps in making data open, each of which we will cover in "
"detail below. These are in very approximate order - many of these can be "
"done simultaneously."
msgstr "Die Offenlegung von Daten umfasst hauptsächlich 4 Schritte, die weiter unten im Einzelnen beschrieben werden. Die Reihenfolge spielt eine untergeordnete Rolle, einige der Schritte können gleichzeitig erfolgen."

# 360556e81fdb4bb9808cacdd2496901f
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:42
msgid ""
"**Choose your dataset(s).** Choose the dataset(s) you plan to make open, "
"though keep in mind you can (and may need to) return to this step if you "
"encounter problems at later stages."
msgstr "**Wählen sie die Daten aus.** Entscheiden sie, welche Daten sie veröffentlichen wollen. Bedenken sie, dass es möglich (und in Einzelfällen auch nötig) sein wird, dass sie diesen Schritt mehrmals durchlaufen."

# 93bfc6cd5af842e29c91607babd2d517
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:43
msgid "**Apply an open license.**"
msgstr "**Vergeben sie eine offene Lizenz.**"

# beb97981364842ac91ea83de28f348cc
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:45
msgid "Determine what intellectual property rights exist in the data."
msgstr "*Stellen sie fest, wer das Urheberrecht an den Daten besitzt, um die es geht."

# 613237afa279406195c9a1595bfc878b
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:46
msgid ""
"Apply a suitable ‘open’ license that licenses all of these rights and "
"supports the definition of openness discussed in the section above on ‘What "
"Open Data’"
msgstr "*Stellen sie die Daten unter eine geeignete Lizenz, die den Nutzern größtmöglichen Spielraum beim Umgang mit den Daten einräumt und den Anforderungen an Offenheit genügt. Mehr dazu erfahren sie im Abschnitt ‘What Open Data’"

# 50184ce48a494ca48ebaa4a388944ad3
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:47
msgid ""
"NB: if you can't do this go back to step 1 and try a different dataset."
msgstr "*Falls das nicht möglich ist, gehen sie zurück zu Schritt 1 und suchen sie eine andere Datensammlung."

# a98f0e167ac744c287e40c6d06515863
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:49
msgid ""
"**Make the data available** - in bulk and in a useful format. You may also "
"wish to consider alternative ways of making it available such as via an API."
msgstr "**Machen sie die Daten verfügbar** - als Massen-Download und in nützlichen Formaten. Bedenken sie auch die Veröffentlichung auf alternativen Wegen wie z.B. über eine API."

# a51d62b957164bfba218d5916caf7b8e
#: how-to-open-up-data/index.rst:50
msgid ""
"**Make it discoverable** - post on the web and perhaps organize a central "
"catalogue to list your open datasets."
msgstr "**Machen sie die Daten auffindbar** - verlinken sie im Web auf ihre Daten. Ziehen sie die erstellung eines zentralen Datenkatalogs in Betracht, in dem alle Datenangebote gelistet werden."

# 9ebce29e9df446a79f7a0262f74913f7
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:3
msgid "Make Data Available (Technical Openness)"
msgstr "Machen sie die Daten verfügbar (technische Offenheit)"

# 8b0e3e1f3dc84afeabfe8d130ed17d14
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:6
msgid ""
":term:`Open data` needs to be technically open as well as legally open. "
"Specifically, the data needs be available in bulk in a :term:`machine-"
"readable` format."
msgstr "Daten sind offen, wenn sie sowohl technisch als auch juristisch offen sind. Die technischen Aspekte im einzelnen sind:"

# a9362007b4c5412f9f30653c2e054013
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:11
msgid ""
"Data should be priced at no more than a reasonable cost of reproduction, "
"preferably as a free download from the Internet. This pricing model is "
"achieved because your agency should not undertake any cost when it provides "
"data for use."
msgstr "Verfügbar - zu einem höchstens geringen Kostenaufwand, der die Reproduktionskosten deckt, bevorzugt als kostenloser Download über das Intenet. Grundsätzlich gilt: Veröffentlichen sie ihre Daten im Internet, wenn immer möglich."

# ee2961781c2740cb8dd35e876351b3d2
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:17
msgid ""
"The data should be available as a complete set. If you have a register which"
" is collected under statue, the entire register should be available for "
"download. A web API or similar service may also be very useful, but they are"
" not a substitutes for bulk access."
msgstr "Als Massenware Die Daten sollten als Gesamt-Download verfügbar sein. (Eine Webservice-API zum gezielten Abruf einzelner Datensätze kann nützlich sein, sollte aber nicht den Gesamt-Download ersetzen.)"

# 544b9a8614c940e6a874f42ea2ca46c8
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:23
msgid ""
"Re-use of data held by the public sector should not be subject to patent "
"restrictions. More importantly, making sure that you are providng machine-"
"readable formats allows for greatest re-use. To illustrate this, consider "
"statistics published as :abbr:`PDF (Portable Document Format, often used for"
" high quality printing)` documents. While these statistics can be read by "
"humans, they are very hard for a computer to use. This greatly limits the "
"ability for others to reuse that data."
msgstr "In einem offenen, maschinenlesbaren Format Maschinenlesbarkeit ist wichtig, weil es die Weiterverwendung deutlich erleichtert. Beispielsweise sind Tabellen in PDF-Dokumenten für menschliche Nutzer gut lesbar, aber für Computerprogramme ist es oft sehr schwer, fehlerfreie Daten mit den korrekten Spalten- und Zeilenzuordnungen aus solchen PDFs zu bekommen."

# 0bbd2febe32547a7aefcd8dc16384444
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:31
msgid "Here are a few policies that will be of great benefit:"
msgstr "Die Hauptsache sollte sein:"

# e03231824b3b446d94b9779bad6f7caf
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:33
msgid "keep it simple,"
msgstr "Halten sie es einfach, "

# 45242cae65cc450cb268a99787e015b4
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:34
msgid "move fast, and"
msgstr "seien sie schnell "

# c546750512534295a558f0a40f352f97
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:35
msgid "be pragmatic"
msgstr "und pragmatisch."

# 825b39490a4c4c0fa54706a7f28e9923
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:37
msgid ""
"In particular it is better to give out raw data now than perfect data in six"
" months' time."
msgstr "Es ist besser, heute Rohdaten zu veröffentlichen, als perfekte Daten erst in sechs Monaten."

# dbedc2f65cf643ce8c00d6f846be45be
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:40
msgid ""
"There are many different ways to make data available to others. The most "
"natural in the Internet age being online publication. There are many "
"variations tor this model. At its most basic, agencies make their data "
"available via their websites and a central catalogue directs visitors to "
"appropriate the appropriate source.  However, there are alternatives."
msgstr "Es gibt viele Möglichkeiten, um Daten verfügbar zu machen. Im Zeitalter des Internets ist es naheliegend, das Internet als Weg für die Verteilung zu wählen. Je nachdem, wie umfangreich die Daten sind, die sie zur Verfügung stellen wollen, könnten jedoch auch andere Wege wie DVDs oder USB-Speicher eine Rolle spielen."

# 1f02b9e985874a0b8d050894201fd080
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:46
msgid ""
"When :term:`connectivity` is limited or the size of the data are extremely "
"large, distribution via other formats, can be warranted. This section will "
"also discuss alternatives, which can act to keep prices very low."
msgstr "Was den Online-Kanal betrifft, stehen verschiedene Möglichkeiten zur Auswahl. Die Daten können auf Webseiten (HTML) angezeigt werden (was in der Regel nicht optimale Maschinenlesbarkeit gewährleistet), per Dateidownload abrufbar sein oder in Form einer Webservice-Schnittstelle (API)."

# 2e1103eed3b748199a5aed1bed8b951a
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:51
msgid "Online methods"
msgstr "Downloads in einfachen, universell maschinenlesbaren Formaten wie XML und CSV stellen sicher, dass eine möglichst breite Nutzergruppe die Daten weiterverwenden kann."

# 93aa2004554a47b381fd6af08fca6cb0
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:54
msgid "via your existing website"
msgstr "Ist die Downloadmöglichkeit sicher gestellt, kann darüber hinaus mit einer Webservice API erreicht werden, dass Nutzer genau die Daten abfragen, die sie benötigen."

# 56cae75e80064abe845ba974e8527375
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:56
msgid ""
"The system which will be most familiar to your web content teams is to "
"provide files for download from webpages. Just as you currently provide "
"access to discussion documents, data files are perfectly happy to be made "
"available this way."
msgstr " So können beispielsweise bei sich ständig erweiternden Zeitreihend die neusten Datensätze geladen werden, ohne dass ein Komplett-Download nötig ist."

# 5a87a9108fa9486fa99f7be2e0178fc0
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:61
msgid ""
"One difficulty with this approach is that it is very difficult for an "
"outsider to discover where to find updated information. This option places "
"quite a bit of burden on the people creating tools with your data."
msgstr "Die Auswahl von universellen und maschinenlesbaren Formaten ist besonders wichtig, da dies großen Einfluss auf die weitere Verwendbarkeit der Daten hat."

# ab59ea70b49d4bbd9df806cfefd7fbf6
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:67
msgid "via 3rd party sites"
msgstr "Optimal lesbare Formate erlauben anderen weit mehr, als ihre Daten bloß anzusehen. Es ermöglicht beispielsweise, dass man die Daten mit anderen Daten in Beziehung setzt, durch Algorithmen auswertet und Fehler aufspürt, sie in anderen Speichern archiviert etc."

# 04fbb1751de44a5d8ab743f539256ca2
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:69
msgid ""
"Many repositories have become hubs of data in particular fields. For "
"example, pachube.com is designed to connect people with sensors to those who"
" wish to access data from them. Sites like Infochimps.com and Talis.com "
"allow public sector agencies to store massive quantities of data for free."
msgstr ""

# 100ac1aac04c402ab18c643d2967e388
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:75
msgid ""
"Third party sites can be very useful. The main reason for this is that they "
"have already pooled together a community of interested people and other sets"
" of data. When your data is part of these platforms, a a type of positive "
"compound interest is created."
msgstr ""

# 0990ad1566c649d8a1898e8ce05f992e
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:80
msgid ""
"Wholesale data platforms already provide the infrastructure which can "
"support the demand. They often provide analytics and usage information. For "
"public sector agencies, they are generally free."
msgstr ""

# c7fa67b366f043a580b3992a809b6320
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:84
msgid ""
"These platforms can have two costs. The first is independence. Your agency "
"needs to be able to yield control to others. This is often politically, "
"legally or operationally difficult. The second cost may be openness. Ensure "
"that your data platform is agnostic of who can access it. Software "
"developers and scientists use many operating sytems, from smart phones to "
"supercomputers. They should all be able to access the data."
msgstr ""

# c1e6b030820c4219a62236333cdf64f5
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:94
msgid "via FTP servers"
msgstr ""

# be82f1bc26d444e897c37249d8b6f5fc
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:96
msgid ""
"A less fashionable method for providing access to files is via the File "
"Transfer Protocol (FTP). This may be suitable if your audience is technical,"
" such as software developers and scientists. The FTP system works in place "
"of HTTP, but is specifically designed to support file transfers."
msgstr ""

# 4f732d2b6ef24d12a709f177fcb24c8a
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:102
msgid ""
"FTP has fallen out of favour. Rather than providing a website, looking "
"through an FTP server is much like looking through folders on a computer. "
"Therefore, even though it is fit for purpose, there is far less capacity for"
" web development firms to charge for customisation."
msgstr ""

# 8811892b640a4fecaaccc6020b53eacf
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:108
msgid "as torrents"
msgstr ""

# 60121bcd7a4b4d52a6c5ef51bea79e4c
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:110
msgid ""
":term:`BitTorrent` is a system which has become familiar to policy makers "
"because of its association with copyright infringement. BitTorrent uses "
"files called torrents, which work by splitting the cost of distributing "
"files between all of the people accessing those files. Instead of servers "
"becoming overloaded, as the demand increases, so does the supply. This is "
"the reason that this system is so successful for  sharing movies. It is a "
"wonderfully efficient way to distribute very large volumes of data."
msgstr ""

# 3b8d563bcceb4311a73a6cac1aa84552
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:119
msgid "as an API"
msgstr ""

# a08020f3e1274b5dbaf60bd128a35d92
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:121
msgid ""
"Data can be published via an :term:`Application Programming Interface` "
"(API). These interfaces have become very popular. They allow programmers to "
"select specific portions of the data at a time, rather than providing all of"
" the data in bulk as a large file. APIs are typically connected to a "
"database which is being updated in real-time. This means that making "
"information available via an API can ensure that it is up to date."
msgstr ""

# 6d419cd419484494bde7576ea261bd92
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:129
msgid ""
"Publishing raw data in bulk should be the primary concern of all open data "
"intiatives. There are a number of costs to providing an API:"
msgstr ""

# c51b82c416b24dc3a1dc8ca7e8bf0ca5
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:132
msgid ""
"The price. They require much more development and maintainence than "
"providing files."
msgstr ""

# 2c81070da9234ab6a1358fbce917717e
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:134
msgid ""
"The expectations. In order to foster a community of users behind the system,"
" it is important to provide certainty. When things go wrong, you will be "
"expected to incur the costs of fixing them."
msgstr ""

# 9b7bf4eea87246b88769a8a1623beaa0
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:138
msgid "Access to bulk data ensures that:"
msgstr ""

# f02124c8b3df47f19c9c8c00aaa74a70
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:140
msgid ""
"there is no dependency on the original provider of the data, meaning if a "
"restructure or budget cycle changes the situation, the data are still "
"available"
msgstr ""

# 44186b0021414f5994492ae83f3f05d8
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:143
msgid ""
"anyone else can obtain a copy and redistribute it. This reduces the cost of "
"distribution away from the source agency and means that there is no single "
"point of failure."
msgstr ""

# 1963b919c7fe4b62b9ee6b62c9e52b3e
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:146
msgid ""
"others can develop their own services using the data, because they have "
"certainty that the data will not be taken away from them."
msgstr ""

# 733dc01da95f41ddae8f2ebc6c10c042
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:149
msgid ""
"Providing data in bulk allows others to use the data beyond its original "
"purposes. For example, it allows conversion it into a new format, linking "
"with other resources, data to be versioned and archival in multiple places. "
"While the latest version of the data may be made available via an API, raw "
"data should be made available in bulk at regular intervals."
msgstr ""

# c9527811b84a4cec9373ab3e7463dbdf
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:155
msgid ""
"For example, the Eurostat statistical service has a bulk download facility "
"offering over 4000 data files. It is updated twice a day, offers data in "
":term:`Tab-separated values` (TSV) format, and includes documentation about "
"the download facility as well as about the data files."
msgstr ""

# ca47f9f74b3c47028dce5fadca1f67fe
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:160
msgid ""
"Another example is the District of Columbia OCTO’s Data Catalogue, which "
"allows data to be downloaded in CSV and XLS format, in addition to live "
"feeds of the data."
msgstr ""

# f8a110ba78f14a7cbfc335351241be87
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:165
msgid "via the data access protocol"
msgstr ""

# 71dd6e588deb425295b9506b4505dfc9
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:167
msgid ""
":term:`DAP` (Data Access Protocol) is a system for data transfer that was "
"developed for use in meterology and climate science. The system was designed"
" to enable third-parties to access sections of databases stored in some "
"central location. Despite its origins in a particular field, the technology "
"is very generic and can be adapted for data transfer in any area."
msgstr ""

# acc37325616340efa5d88f19c032ebcf
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:174
msgid ""
"Implementing this technology can enable your agency to be experimental with "
"its knowledge. For example, Australia's `Bureau of Meteorology Research "
"Centre`_ provides the following disclaimer on its material:"
msgstr ""

# ffb76dad2b1b4b4a82073b9ecdf7cdbf
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:178
msgid ""
"Please note that the following products ... do not currently form part of "
"the Bureau's standard services in any way."
msgstr ""

# 379f6fc7be9f4f39b547a8fe1a6c3ac1
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:181
msgid ""
"This example demonstrates that it is possible to provide data in raw form "
"without incurring liability for others' use of that data."
msgstr ""

# 4ff03b19748f46a8952a8802ba726ad3
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:187
msgid "via WebDAV"
msgstr ""

# fdf200a93e5d491c836258a8e3036bc8
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:189
msgid ""
"`WebDAV`_, or Web-based Distributed Authoring and Versioning, is an attempt "
"at making the internet a read/write medium. It is a widely supported open "
"standard that supports locking and distributed authorship."
msgstr ""

# 12c7b5eb3a9342748dcb051ab0386722
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:193
msgid ""
"Providing a service such as this could be useful for situations where your "
"agency would like to handle receiving improvements to data that it stores. "
"The agency could provide its original data as the orginal source and then "
"refer to higher-quality, but unverified derivative data source for users "
"with different needs."
msgstr ""

# f132f85b986e4dc39eb38582443cc216
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:202
msgid "Offline methods"
msgstr ""

# 69e564c3de8d4f44b55095f1421ad7fe
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:205
msgid "via optical media"
msgstr ""

# b3b97a2f7da94ad989b73d8ebecd1084
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:207
msgid ""
"Optical media, such as DVDs, are very cheap to produce. However, they tend "
"to lack the capacity that would warrant the manual handling of distributing "
"them. One exception to this is events. If you are hosting an event for "
"developers, such as a hackfest or barcamp, optical media can be the best way"
" to distribute a dataset for use in the venue."
msgstr ""

# e85fc955b08d436babcf73ae386d195c
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:215
msgid "via external hard disk drives"
msgstr ""

# 862409b256264bba8153c8c2d757646a
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:217
msgid ""
"Hard disk drives can be very useful for data transfers in the terabyte "
"range. To support this, you need to have some form of ability to receive "
"funds to cover the purchase, handling and shipping of your data."
msgstr ""

# f2772ea8574c48a6a82f7785dbafdbb2
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-data-available.rst:221
msgid ""
"Be careful to make sure that you are not charging for the data. Instead, "
"your fee should be as close to the actual cost of distribution as possible."
msgstr ""

# ab9bf05d69d1427b91215b26e04b9919
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:3
msgid "Make data discoverable"
msgstr ""

# 21c49a37533c4dd2acf491ff7ca6f0d7
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:5
msgid ""
":term:`Open data` is nothing without users. You need to be able to make sure"
" that people can find the source material. This section will cover different"
" approaches."
msgstr ""

# bdd4a5b611e14cc1977d0e7986a7f9a9
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:9
msgid ""
"The most important thing is to provide a neutral space which is easy which "
"can overcome both inter-agency politics and future budget cycles. "
"Jurisdictional borders, whether sectorial or geographical, can make "
"cooperation difficult. However, there are significant benefits in joining "
"forces. The easier it is for outsiders to discover data, the faster new and "
"useful tools will be built."
msgstr ""

# 25082c4ac7ee4ea3b64d2e3579d87f7a
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:17
msgid "Existing tools"
msgstr ""

# 1acc88709271446eb909c31706b4418d
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:19
msgid ""
"There are a number of tools which are live on the web that are specifically "
"designed to make data most discoverable."
msgstr ""

# d92c7d1ee4a541ccadcc44af6cc9b136
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:22
msgid ""
"The most prominent is CKAN.net. CKAN stands for the Comprehensive Knowledge "
"Archive Network, and is a catalogue of all datasets in the world. The site "
"makes it very easy for developers to find tha material that they're seeking."
msgstr ""

# 2d1ab370a1cf491baa3ac0c91d48d32b
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:26
msgid ""
"In addition, there are dozens of specialist catalogues for different sectors"
" and places. Many scientific communities have created a catalogue system for"
" their fields, as data are often required for publication."
msgstr ""

# e67d4d8266514bf7aa2ff8c281ef1aa4
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:32
msgid "For government"
msgstr ""

# 42cc67b8665f458eb5fa9e7469c3fab1
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:34
msgid ""
"As it has emerged, orthodox practice is for a lead agency to create a "
"catalogue for the government's data. When establishing a catalogue, try to "
"create some structure which many departments can keep their own information "
"current easily."
msgstr ""

# af17ee6f6f384c07af8f2cf17c237a14
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:39
msgid ""
"Resist the urge to build the software to support the catalogue from scratch."
" There are many free and open source software solutions which have been "
"adopted by many dozens of governments already. Investing in another platform"
" will be a waste of resource."
msgstr ""

# 392ac02376824f509dfcd2e01fa784cb
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:44
msgid ""
"There are a few things that most open data catalogues miss. Your programme "
"could consider the following:"
msgstr ""

# 48937e7cccec49aa870783e2af91fc06
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:47
msgid ""
"Providing an avenue to allow the private and community sectors to add their "
"data. It may be worthwhile to think of the catalogue as the region's "
"catalogue, rather than the regional government's."
msgstr ""

# a0da7ac0ec9b4bacae61cdf50a7b32a7
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:50
msgid ""
"Facilitating improvement of the data by allowing derivatives of datasets to "
"be catalogued. For example, someone may geocode addresses and may wish to "
"share those results with everybody. If you only allow single versions of "
"datasets, these improvements remain hidden."
msgstr ""

# fbd18ad2539e496c9dbcdb6e51093123
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:54
msgid ""
"Be tolerant of your data appearing elsewhere. That is, content is likely to "
"be duplicated to communities of interest. If you have river level monitoring"
" data available, then your data may appear in a catalogue for hydrologists."
msgstr ""

# 174548a845ff4c1ea048d8e2be3a2584
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:58
msgid ""
"Ensure that access is equitible. Do not create a priviledged level of access"
" for officials or tenured researchers. This will cause resentment and "
"ultimately undermine the goals that you are seeking to achive."
msgstr ""

# 3380b8d38cbe48cba09d543feb2420fc
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:64
msgid "For civil society"
msgstr ""

# 3c6799a07da54f22a1495c820da29488
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:66
msgid "Be willing to create a supplementary catalogue for non-official data."
msgstr ""

# ae619626021f458b90dcaf7d64d051cc
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:68
msgid ""
"It is very rare for governments to associate with unofficial or non-"
"authoritative sources. Officials have often gone to great expense to ensure "
"that there will not be political embarrasment or other harm caused from "
"misuse or overreliance on data."
msgstr ""

# 35f9bb4a6a054af59e31873702af4fce
#: how-to-open-up-data/make-it-discoverable.rst:73
msgid ""
"Moreover, governments are unlikely to be willing to support activities that "
"mesh their information with information from businesses. Governments are "
"rightfully skeptical of profit motives. Therefore, an independent catalogue "
"for community groups, businesses and others may be warranted."
msgstr ""

