# bf682c62ba894b8987ba424b7a5c6cbc
#: appendix/file-formats.rst:100
msgid ""
"When Authority must exhibit new data - that data has not been exhibited "
"before - you should choose the format that provides the best balance between"
" cost and suitability for purpose. For each format there are some things you"
" should be aware of, and this section aims to affect them."
msgstr ""

# e7dffc60da434da9ae282e78405cd334
#: appendix/file-formats.rst:102
msgid ""
"This section focuses only on how the cut surfaces are best arranged so that "
"machines can access them directly. Advice and guidance about how web sites "
"and web solutions should be designed, you can find elsewhere."
msgstr ""

# 30b3eb521ad84cfcb3445a5e6fe30a1d
#: appendix/file-formats.rst:105
msgid "Web services"
msgstr ""

# f55a5fd0bc50436aab0728d102211fd1
#: appendix/file-formats.rst:107
msgid ""
"For data that change frequently, and where each pull is limited in size, it "
"is very relevant to expose data through web services. There are several ways"
" to create a web service, but some of the most used is SOAP and REST. "
"Generally, SOAP over REST, REST services, but are very easy to develop and "
"use, so it is a widely used standard."
msgstr ""

# 9d49662dbe464170aae1cf963065fe28
#: appendix/file-formats.rst:110
msgid "Database"
msgstr ""

# e9ffd614997c4d6d9cc864b3dfacc3ed
#: appendix/file-formats.rst:112
msgid ""
"Like Web services provide direct database access to access data dynamically."
" Databases have the advantage that they can allow users to put together just"
" the extraction, they are interested in."
